{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-04-12T15:45+0000", "md5": "FDD4C9C16F95F00CD0D6B21707A8DA65", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "TAXREF", "normalizedForm": "TAXREF", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "TAXREF registers all species recorded in metropolitan France and overseas territories, accounting for 260,000+ biological taxa (200,000+ species) along with 570,000+ scientific names. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015553534030914307}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.450580596923828e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015553534030914307}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9979252219200134}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPARQL", "normalizedForm": "SPARQL", "offsetStart": 2, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "A SPARQL micro-service is a SPARQL endpoint that wraps a Web API service; it typically produces a small, resource-centric RDF graph by invoking the Web API and transforming the response into RDF triples.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00011271238327026367}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0009307861328125}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "TAXREF", "normalizedForm": "TAXREF", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 10}, "context": "The TAXREF-Web application compares data available in TAXREF with corresponding data from third-party data sources, points out disagreements and allows biologists to add, remove or amend TAXREF accordingly. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00032329559326171875}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002808570861816406}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015553534030914307}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9979252219200134}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPARQL", "normalizedForm": "SPARQL", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "We developed SPARQL micro-services to wrap the Web APIs of GBIF, World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS), FishBase, Index Fungorum, Pan-European Species directories Infrastructure (PESI), ZooBank, International Plant Names Index (IPNI), EoL, Tropicos and Sandre. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00022792816162109375}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4733121395111084}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "TAXREF", "normalizedForm": "TAXREF", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 25}, "context": "This requires that TAXREF-Web developers write a specific piece of code for each considered Web API to align TAXREF representation with the Web API counterpart. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.008466839790344238}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005283951759338379}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015553534030914307}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9979252219200134}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPARQL", "normalizedForm": "SPARQL", "offsetStart": 28, "offsetEnd": 34}, "context": "A SPARQL micro-service is a SPARQL endpoint that wraps a Web API service; it typically produces a small, resource-centric RDF graph by invoking the Web API and transforming the response into RDF triples.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00011271238327026367}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0009307861328125}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPARQL", "normalizedForm": "SPARQL", "offsetStart": 29, "offsetEnd": 35}, "context": "In addition, we leverage the SPARQL Micro-Service architecture (Michel et al. 2018), a lightweight approach to query Web APIs using SPARQL.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.91974937915802}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPARQL", "normalizedForm": "SPARQL", "offsetStart": 39, "offsetEnd": 45}, "context": "Second, wrapping all these Web APIs in SPARQL micro-services \"suddenly\" makes them technically and semantically interoperable, since they all represent resources (taxa, habitats, traits, etc.) in a common manner. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006282925605773926}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010317564010620117}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0132789611816406e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "TAXREF", "normalizedForm": "TAXREF", "offsetStart": 54, "offsetEnd": 60}, "context": "The TAXREF-Web application compares data available in TAXREF with corresponding data from third-party data sources, points out disagreements and allows biologists to add, remove or amend TAXREF accordingly. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00032329559326171875}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002808570861816406}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015553534030914307}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9979252219200134}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "TAXREF-Web", "normalizedForm": "TAXREF-Web", "offsetStart": 59, "offsetEnd": 69}, "context": "In this presentation, we report on a new implementation of TAXREF-Web that harnesses the Linked Data standards: Resource Description Framework (RDF), the Semantic Web format to represent knowledge graphs, and SPARQL, the W3C standard to query RDF graphs. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00018930435180664062}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.940696716308594e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00018930435180664062}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.940696716308594e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "TAXREF", "normalizedForm": "TAXREF", "offsetStart": 96, "offsetEnd": 102}, "context": "We present several concrete cases in which we use this approach to detect disagreements between TAXREF and the aforementioned data sources, with respect to taxonomic information (author, synonymy, vernacular names, classification, taxonomic rank), habitats, bibliographic references, species interactions and life traits.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0035480856895446777}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9979252219200134}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.172325134277344e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015553534030914307}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9979252219200134}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "TAXREF", "normalizedForm": "TAXREF", "offsetStart": 109, "offsetEnd": 115}, "context": "This requires that TAXREF-Web developers write a specific piece of code for each considered Web API to align TAXREF representation with the Web API counterpart.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.008466839790344238}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005283951759338379}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015553534030914307}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9979252219200134}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPARQL", "normalizedForm": "SPARQL", "offsetStart": 132, "offsetEnd": 138}, "context": "In addition, we leverage the SPARQL Micro-Service architecture (Michel et al. 2018), a lightweight approach to query Web APIs using SPARQL.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.91974937915802}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPARQL", "normalizedForm": "SPARQL", "offsetStart": 137, "offsetEnd": 143}, "context": "Consequently, the integration task is simplified: confronting data from multiple sources essentially consists of writing the appropriate SPARQL queries, thus making easier web application development and maintenance.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003031492233276367}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005859136581420898}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00817418098449707}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997309446334839}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "TAXREF", "normalizedForm": "TAXREF", "offsetStart": 187, "offsetEnd": 193}, "context": "The TAXREF-Web application compares data available in TAXREF with corresponding data from third-party data sources, points out disagreements and allows biologists to add, remove or amend TAXREF accordingly.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00032329559326171875}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002808570861816406}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015553534030914307}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9979252219200134}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001518726348876953}}}, {"type": "software", "software-typ